    "In addition, abnormal fatty acid metabolism is related to the occurrence and development of tumors, such as liver cancer, gastric cancer, ovarian cancer, and cervical cancer (88) (89) (90).",
    "The sterol regulatory element binding protein pathway in lipid metabolism controls lipid synthesis in cells (91).",
    "In Figure 2, De novo synthesis of lipids can promote high expression of PD-L1 and tumor immune suppression through palmitoylation of the immune checkpoint PD-L1 (92).",
    "In addition, PD-1 stimulates the AMPactivated protein kinase activity, inhibits glycolysis, and promotes fatty acid oxidation by upregulating activated CD4 + T cells, thereby inhibiting the development of effector T cells (93).",
    "The lipid transporter protein CD36 mediates intracellular fatty acid uptake and lipid droplet growth (94)."
